The expression is somewhat changed in passing through the lips of Cato, but the general thought is the same. In the Cyropaedia Cyrus has stated his desire that the elder son should rule after him, but should, if he need a colleague, associate the younger with him in the government. He urges his sons to honor one another, and thus show their regard for him after his death.
